# Pull-to-Refresh & Pagination Guide

## Quick Reference

| Data Type | Widget | Notifier |
|-----------|--------|----------|
| Non-paginated | `RefreshableContent<T>` | `BaseNotifier<T>` |
| Paginated | `PaginatedListView<T>` | `PaginatedNotifier<T>` |

---

## Non-Paginated: RefreshableContent

### 1. Create Notifier

**Pattern A: FutureProvider Chain (for early-load screens like Dashboard)**

Use when feature loads immediately after login - services may still be initializing:

```dart
class DashboardNotifier extends BaseNotifier<Dashboard> {
  final Ref _ref;

  DashboardNotifier(this._ref) : super();

  @override
  Future<Result<Dashboard>> fetchData({Map<String, dynamic>? params}) async {
    try {
      // Lazily await the use case - safe even if not ready
      final useCase = await _ref.read(getDashboardUseCaseProvider.future);
      return await useCase.execute(
        statsType: params?['statsType'] as DashboardStatsType?,
        applicationType: params?['applicationType'] as ApplicationType?,
      );
    } catch (e) {
      return Failure(message: 'Failed to initialize: $e');
    }
  }
}

// All providers are FutureProvider - handles async safely
final dashboardServiceProvider = FutureProvider<DashboardService>((ref) async {
  final client = await ref.watch(apiClientProvider.future);
  return client.getService<DashboardService>();
});

final dashboardRepositoryProvider = FutureProvider<DashboardRepository>((ref) async {
  final service = await ref.watch(dashboardServiceProvider.future);
  return DashboardRepository(service);
});

final getDashboardUseCaseProvider = FutureProvider<GetDashboardUseCase>((ref) async {
  final repository = await ref.watch(dashboardRepositoryProvider.future);
  return GetDashboardUseCase(repository);
});

final dashboardProvider = StateNotifierProvider<DashboardNotifier, BaseState<Dashboard>>((ref) {
  return DashboardNotifier(ref);
});
```

**Pattern B: .requireValue (for lazy-load screens where services are ready)**

Use only when you're 100% certain the service has already loaded:

```dart
class NotificationNotifier extends PaginatedNotifier<Notification> {
  final GetNotificationsUseCase _useCase;

  NotificationNotifier(this._useCase) : super();

  @override
  Future<Result<PaginatedList<Notification>>> fetchPage({...}) async {
    return await _useCase.execute(...);
  }
}

// Service is FutureProvider, rest use .requireValue
final notificationServiceProvider = FutureProvider<NotificationService>((ref) async {
  final client = await ref.watch(apiClientProvider.future);
  return client.getService<NotificationService>();
});

// ⚠️ Only safe if service is guaranteed to be loaded!
final notificationRepositoryProvider = Provider<NotificationRepository>((ref) {
  final service = ref.watch(notificationServiceProvider).requireValue;
  return NotificationRepository(service);
});
```

### 2. Use Widget

```dart
class DashboardScreen extends ConsumerStatefulWidget {
  @override
  ConsumerState<DashboardScreen> createState() => _DashboardScreenState();
}

class _DashboardScreenState extends ConsumerState<DashboardScreen> {
  @override
  void initState() {
    super.initState();
    WidgetsBinding.instance.addPostFrameCallback((_) {
      ref.read(dashboardProvider.notifier).loadDashboard();
    });
  }

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Scaffold(
      body: RefreshableContent<Dashboard>(
        state: ref.watch(dashboardProvider),
        onRefresh: () => ref.read(dashboardProvider.notifier).loadDashboard(),
        onRetry: () => ref.read(dashboardProvider.notifier).loadDashboard(),
        childBuilder: (dashboard) => SingleChildScrollView(
          child: _buildContent(dashboard),
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}
```

